===Etymology===
{{ML.}} ''nadir'', from {{Arab.}} 
{{ARchar|[[نظير اسمت|نَظِيرُ السَّمْت]]}} ''naẓīru as-samt,'' nadir, properly "the point opposite 
{{ARchar|[[سمت|السَمْتُ]]}} (''as-samt'') the zenith", in which 
{{ARchar|[[نظير|نَظِير]]}} ''naẓīr'' means "counterpart, corresponding to".

===Noun===
'''nadir''' (''plural'' '''nadirs''')

#The point of the heavens, or lower hemisphere, directly opposite the zenith; inferior pole of the horizon; point of the celestial sphere directly under the place where we stand.
#(''figurative'') The lowest point; time of greatest depression.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*"The seventh century is the '''nadir''' of the human mind in Europe." &mdash; Hallam.
#(''astronomy'') The axis of a projected conical shadow (e.g. the nadir of the sun is the axis of the conical shadow projected by the Earth)

